author: eTN Managing Editor
title: Qatar Airways is adding another city in Australia to its non stop network from Doha
text:
Qatar Airways is adding another city in Australia to its non stop network from Doha   
Oct 13, 2015 eTN   
Qatar Airways today unveiled the launch of another Australian destination, with daily non-stop scheduled flights between Doha and Adelaide due to commence on May 2, 2016. 
The airline has embarked on a major expansion in Australia, just recently announcing the launch of daily flights to Sydney from 1st of March next year. 
Adelaide will also be the first destination in Australia to which Qatar Airways will fly its A350 aircraft. Flying a long-haul service to Adelaide, which is a key business and leisure destination in southern Australia, will enable Qatar Airways to maximize the A350â€™s efficiency and performance.
